<?xml version='1.0' encoding='windows-1252'?>

<xs:schema attributeFormDefault="unqualified" elementFormDefault="qualified" targetNamespace="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
	<xs:annotation>
		<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
      DCMES 1.1 XML Schema
      XML Schema for http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/ namespace

      Created 2008-02-11

      Created by 

      Tim Cole (t-cole3@uiuc.edu)
      Tom Habing (thabing@uiuc.edu)
      Jane Hunter (jane@dstc.edu.au)
      Pete Johnston (p.johnston@ukoln.ac.uk),
      Carl Lagoze (lagoze@cs.cornell.edu)

      This schema declares XML elements for the 15 DC elements from the
      http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/ namespace.

      It defines a complexType SimpleLiteral which permits mixed content 
      and makes the xml:lang attribute available. It disallows child elements by
      use of minOcccurs/maxOccurs.

      However, this complexType does permit the derivation of other complexTypes
      which would permit child elements.

      All elements are declared as substitutable for the abstract element any, 
      which means that the default type for all elements is dc:SimpleLiteral.

    </xs:documentation>
	</xs:annotation>
	<xs:import namespace="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace" schemaLocation="xml.xsd"/>
	<xs:complexType mixed="true" name="SimpleLiteral">
		<xs:annotation>
			<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
            This is the default type for all of the DC elements.
            It permits text content only with optional
            xml:lang attribute.
            Text is allowed because mixed="true", but sub-elements
            are disallowed because minOccurs="0" and maxOccurs="0" 
            are on the xs:any tag.

    	    This complexType allows for restriction or extension permitting
            child elements.
    	</xs:documentation>
		</xs:annotation>
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:restriction base="xs:anyType">
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:any maxOccurs="0" minOccurs="0" processContents="lax"/>
				</xs:sequence>
				<xs:attribute ref="xml:lang" use="optional"/>
			</xs:restriction>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="elementContainer">
		<xs:annotation>
			<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
    		This complexType is included as a convenience for schema authors who need to define a root
    		or container element for all of the DC elements.
    	</xs:documentation>
		</xs:annotation>
		<xs:choice>
			<xs:group ref="elementsGroup"/>
		</xs:choice>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:group name="elementsGroup">
		<xs:annotation>
			<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
    	    This group is included as a convenience for schema authors
            who need to refer to all the elements in the 
            http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/ namespace.
    	</xs:documentation>
		</xs:annotation>
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:choice maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0">
				<xs:element ref="any"/>
			</xs:choice>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:group>
	<xs:element name="title" substitutionGroup="any"/>
	<xs:element name="creator" substitutionGroup="any"/>
	<xs:element name="subject" substitutionGroup="any"/>
	<xs:element name="description" substitutionGroup="any"/>
	<xs:element name="publisher" substitutionGroup="any"/>
	<xs:element name="contributor" substitutionGroup="any"/>
	<xs:element name="date" substitutionGroup="any"/>
	<xs:element name="type" substitutionGroup="any"/>
	<xs:element name="format" substitutionGroup="any"/>
	<xs:element name="identifier" substitutionGroup="any"/>
	<xs:element name="source" substitutionGroup="any"/>
	<xs:element name="language" substitutionGroup="any"/>
	<xs:element name="relation" substitutionGroup="any"/>
	<xs:element name="coverage" substitutionGroup="any"/>
	<xs:element name="rights" substitutionGroup="any"/>
	<xs:element abstract="true" name="any" type="SimpleLiteral"/>
</xs:schema>

<xs:schema elementFormDefault="qualified" targetNamespace="http://www.transport.alstom.com/GenericADM/1" vc:minVersion="1.1" version="0.1" xmlns:GenericADM="http://www.transport.alstom.com/GenericADM/1" xmlns:rail="http://www.railml.org/schemas/2016" xmlns:vc="http://www.w3.org/2007/XMLSchema-versioning" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
	<xs:import namespace="http://www.railml.org/schemas/2016" schemaLocation="railML.xsd"/>
	<xs:complexType name="eLogicalElements">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="routes" type="GenericADM:eRoutes"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="tVDSections" type="GenericADM:eTVDSections"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="stablingAreas" type="GenericADM:eStablingAreas"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="turnbackAreas" type="GenericADM:eTurnbackAreas"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="distanceFromReferencedDesignElements" type="GenericADM:eDistanceFromReferencedDesignElements"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="switchPointAndPositions" type="GenericADM:eSwitchPointAndPositions"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="phaseAreas" type="GenericADM:ePhaseAreas"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="pageAreas" type="GenericADM:ePageAreas"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="scaleAreas" type="GenericADM:eScaleAreas"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="civilWorkAreas" type="GenericADM:eCivilWorkAreas"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="specificLogicalAreas" type="GenericADM:eSpecificLogicalAreas"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="specificPolygonAreas" type="GenericADM:eSpecificPolygonAreas"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="RegulationElements">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="services" type="GenericADM:eServices">
				<xs:annotation>
					<xs:documentation>A Service represents the complete set of movements that a given train must perform one after the other in order to satisfy the production of services scheduled by the RegulationElements</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
			</xs:element>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="insertions" type="GenericADM:eInsertions">
				<xs:annotation>
					<xs:documentation>List of patterns to realize the Insertion</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
			</xs:element>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="withdrawals" type="GenericADM:eWithdrawals">
				<xs:annotation>
					<xs:documentation>List of patterns to realize the Withdrawal</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
			</xs:element>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="patterns" type="GenericADM:ePatterns">
				<xs:annotation>
					<xs:documentation>A Pattern is a static set of ElementaryPaths defined during data preparation. It is part of a Service and used to build on-line Trips and calculate the train movements</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
			</xs:element>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="elementaryPaths" type="GenericADM:eElementaryPaths">
				<xs:annotation>
					<xs:documentation>ElementaryPath is the train movement description from one stopping area to a next stopping area. The granularity shall be such that there is only possible combination to go from the starting to stopping area</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
			</xs:element>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eInfrastructureForInstallation">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="distancesFromReferencedInstallationElements" type="GenericADM:eDistancesFromReferencedInstallationElements"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="distancesFromReferenceTrackSurveyElements" type="GenericADM:eDistancesFromReferenceTrackSurveyElements"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="cableDuctTrackCrossingGroups" type="GenericADM:eCableDuctTrackCrossingGroups"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="cables" type="GenericADM:eCables"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eArchitecture">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="trackSideArchitecture" type="GenericADM:eTrackSideArchitecture"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="onBoardArchitecture" type="GenericADM:eOnBoardArchitecture"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eTrackSideArchitecture">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="equipmentRooms" type="GenericADM:eEquipmentRooms"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="assemblyConfigurations" type="GenericADM:eAssemblyConfigurations"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="backboneNetworks" type="GenericADM:eBackboneNetworks"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="backboneNetworkConnections" type="GenericADM:eBackboneNetworkConnections"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="physicalLinks" type="GenericADM:ePhysicalLinks"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="physicalLinkCharacteristics" type="GenericADM:ePhysicalLinkCharacteristics"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eEquipmentRooms">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="1" name="equipmentRoom" type="GenericADM:tEquipmentRoom"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tEquipmentRoom">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="GenericADM:tArchitectureElement">
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="assemblies" type="GenericADM:eAssemblies"/>
				</xs:sequence>
				<xs:attribute name="equipmentRoomInfraRef" type="rail:tGenericRef" use="required"/>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eAssemblies">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="1" name="assembly" type="GenericADM:tAssembly"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tAssembly">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="GenericADM:tArchitectureElement">
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="cubicles" type="GenericADM:eCubicles"/>
				</xs:sequence>
				<xs:attribute name="assemblyConfigurationRef" type="rail:tGenericRef" use="optional"/>
				<xs:attribute name="assemblyType" type="xs:string" use="optional"/>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eCubicles">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="1" name="cubicle" type="GenericADM:tCubicle"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tCubicle">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="GenericADM:tArchitectureElement">
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="equipments" type="GenericADM:eEquipments"/>
				</xs:sequence>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eEquipments">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="1" name="equipment" type="GenericADM:tArchitectureEquipment"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tArchitectureEquipment">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="GenericADM:tArchitectureElement">
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="ethernetPorts" type="GenericADM:eEthernetPorts">
						<xs:annotation>
							<xs:documentation>Defines an ethernet physical interface</xs:documentation>
						</xs:annotation>
					</xs:element>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="serialPorts" type="GenericADM:eSerialPorts">
						<xs:annotation>
							<xs:documentation>Defines a serial physical interface</xs:documentation>
						</xs:annotation>
					</xs:element>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="geoRedundancy" type="GenericADM:tGeoRedundancy"/>
					<xs:choice>
						<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="racks" type="GenericADM:eRacks"/>
						<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="lRUs" type="GenericADM:eLRUs"/>
					</xs:choice>
				</xs:sequence>
				<xs:attribute name="subsystemType" type="GenericADM:tEnumSubsystemType" use="required"/>
				<xs:attribute name="equipmentType" type="GenericADM:tEnumEquipmentType" use="required"/>
				<xs:attribute name="equipmentSubType" type="xs:string" use="optional"/>
				<xs:attribute name="hostedInAssembly" type="xs:boolean" use="optional"/>
				<xs:attribute name="hostedInCubicle" type="xs:boolean" use="optional"/>
				<xs:attribute name="positionInCubicle" type="xs:integer" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Position starting from the bottom of the cubicle</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="equipmentHeight" type="xs:integer" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Defines the height of the equipment in U</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="PRODUCT_GID_32" type="GenericADM:tHEX32_N_0F" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Indicates the Product Geographical Identifier of some product devices types (4 bytes)</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="PRODUCT_GID_64" type="GenericADM:tHEX64_N_0F" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Indicates the Product Geographical Identifier of some product devices types (8 bytes)</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="MooNParametersDefinitionRef" type="rail:tGenericRef" use="optional"/>
				<xs:attribute name="SMOCParametersDefinitionRef" type="rail:tGenericRef" use="optional"/>
				<xs:attribute name="NOMINAL_MOON_ID" type="GenericADM:tHEX32_N_0F" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Identification of the Nominal MooN instance to be used as a SIL4 ID in the messages for Geographical redundancy.</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="RESERVE_MOON_ID" type="GenericADM:tHEX32_N_0F" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Identification of the Remote MooNRESERVE MooN to be used as a SIL4 ID in the messages for Geographical redundancy.</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eAssemblyConfigurations">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="1" name="assemblyConfiguration" type="GenericADM:tAssemblyConfiguration"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="ePhysicalLinks">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="1" name="physicalLink" type="GenericADM:tPhysicalLink"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="ePhysicalLinkCharacteristics">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="1" name="physicalLinkCharacteristic" type="GenericADM:tPhysicalLinkCharacteristic"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eOnBoardArchitecture">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="trains" type="GenericADM:eTrains"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="trainConfigurations" type="GenericADM:eTrainConfigurations"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="backboneNetworks" type="GenericADM:eBackboneNetworks"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="backboneNetworkConnections" type="GenericADM:eBackboneNetworkConnections"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="physicalLinks" type="GenericADM:ePhysicalLinks"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="physicalLinkCharacteristics" type="GenericADM:ePhysicalLinkCharacteristics"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eTrains">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="1" name="train" type="GenericADM:tTrain"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tTrain">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="GenericADM:tOnBoardArchitectureElement">
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="cars" type="GenericADM:eCars"/>
				</xs:sequence>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tAssemblyConfiguration">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="GenericADM:tArchitectureElement">
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="cubicleConfigurations" type="GenericADM:eCubicleConfigurations"/>
				</xs:sequence>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eCubicleConfigurations">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="1" name="cubicleConfiguration" type="GenericADM:tCubicleConfiguration"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tCubicleConfiguration">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="rail:tElementWithIDAndName">
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="equipmentConfigurations" type="GenericADM:eEquipmentConfigurations"/>
				</xs:sequence>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eEquipmentConfigurations">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="1" name="equipmentConfiguration" type="GenericADM:tEquipmentConfiguration"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tEquipmentConfiguration">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="rail:tElementWithIDAndName">

					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="rackConfigurations" type="GenericADM:eRackConfigurations"/>
				</xs:sequence>
				<xs:attribute name="equipmentType" type="GenericADM:tEnumEquipmentType" use="optional"/>
				<xs:attribute name="equipmentSubType" type="xs:string" use="optional"/>
				<xs:attribute name="hostedInCubicle" type="xs:boolean" use="optional"/>
				<xs:attribute name="hostedInAssembly" type="xs:boolean" use="optional"/>
				<xs:attribute name="positionInCubicle" type="xs:integer" use="optional"/>
				<xs:attribute name="equipmentHeight" type="xs:integer" use="optional"/>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eEthernetPorts">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="8" minOccurs="0" name="ethernetPort" type="GenericADM:tEthernetPort"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eSerialPorts">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="4" minOccurs="0" name="serialPort" type="GenericADM:tSerialPort"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tPhysicalLink">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="rail:tElementWithIDAndName">
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:choice>
						<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="connectedPairOfPortRefs" type="GenericADM:eConnectedPairOfPortRefs"/>
						<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="connectedEquipmentToBackboneNetwork" type="GenericADM:eConnectedEquipmentToBackboneNetwork"/>
					</xs:choice>
				</xs:sequence>
				<xs:attribute name="physicalLinkCharacteristicRef" type="rail:tGenericRef" use="required"/>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tPhysicalLinkCharacteristic">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="rail:tElementWithIDAndName">
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="physicalLinkEthernetCharacteristics" type="GenericADM:tPhysicalLinkEthernetCharacteristics"/>
				</xs:sequence>
				<xs:attribute name="subnetColor" type="GenericADM:tEnumSubnetColor" use="required"/>
				<xs:attribute name="physicalLinkType" type="GenericADM:tEnumPhysicalLinkType" use="required"/>
				<xs:attribute name="connectionType" type="GenericADM:tEnumConnectionType" use="required"/>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tPhysicalLinkEthernetCharacteristics">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="portAddrRange" type="GenericADM:tPortAddrRange"/>
		</xs:sequence>
		<xs:attribute name="subnetMask" type="xs:string" use="required"/>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tPortAddrRange">
		<xs:attribute name="portAddrRangeMin" type="xs:string" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="portAddrRangeMax" type="xs:string" use="required"/>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tArchitectureElement">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="rail:tElementWithIDAndName"/>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tOnBoardArchitectureElement">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="rail:tElementWithIDAndName"/>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tEthernetPort">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="rail:tElementWithIDAndName">

						</xs:annotation>

				</xs:sequence>

					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="emitterEquipmentType" type="GenericADM:tEnumEquipmentType" use="required"/>
				<xs:attribute name="receiverEquipmentType" type="GenericADM:tEnumEquipmentType" use="required"/>

	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tApplicationProtocolLayerITFConfiguration">

			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="fsfb2ITFParameters" type="GenericADM:tFsfb2ITFParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="nvfb2ITFParameters" type="GenericADM:tNvfb2ITFParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="euroradioITFParameters" type="GenericADM:tEuroradioPlusITFParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="sntpITFParameters" type="GenericADM:tSntpITFParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="snmpITFParameters" type="GenericADM:tSnmpITFParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="impITFParameters" type="GenericADM:tImpITFParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="hilcITFParameters" type="GenericADM:tHilcITFParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="saatITFParameters" type="GenericADM:tSaatITFParameters"/>
		</xs:choice>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tFsfb2ITFParameters">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="fsfb2Global" type="GenericADM:tFsfb2Global"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="uevolGlobal" type="GenericADM:tUevolGlobal"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="srttParameters" type="GenericADM:tSrttParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="geoRddParameters" type="GenericADM:tGeoRddParameters"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tEuroradioPlusITFParameters">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="saiParameters" type="GenericADM:tSaiParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="tleParameters" type="GenericADM:tTleParameters"/>
		</xs:sequence>
		<xs:attribute name="safetyProtocol" type="xs:boolean" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates, for each peripheral, if the whole safety protocol (TLE + SL + SAI) has to be respected or not (only redundancy (TLE)).</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tNvfb2ITFParameters"/>
	<xs:complexType name="tSntpITFParameters"/>
	<xs:complexType name="tSnmpITFParameters">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="managerConfiguration" type="GenericADM:tManagerConfiguration"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tApplicationProtocolLayerConfiguration">
		<xs:choice>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="fsfb2Parameters" type="GenericADM:tFsfb2Parameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="nvfb2Parameters" type="GenericADM:tNvfb2Parameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="euroradioPlusParameters" type="GenericADM:tEuroradioPlusParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="sntpParameters" type="GenericADM:tSntpParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="snmpParameters" type="GenericADM:tSnmpParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="impParameters" type="GenericADM:tImpParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="hilcParameters" type="GenericADM:tHILCParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="webServicesParameters" type="GenericADM:tWebServicesParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="integrityParameters" type="GenericADM:tIntegrityParameters"/>
		</xs:choice>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tFsfb2Parameters">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="fsfb2Address" type="GenericADM:tFsfb2Address"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="dataVersionNumbers" type="GenericADM:eDataVersionNumbers"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="uevolParameters" type="GenericADM:tUevolParameters"/>
		</xs:sequence>
		<xs:attribute name="id" type="rail:tGenericID" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="dataNumber" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="sourceIdentifierNumber1" type="GenericADM:tHexa" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="sequenceInitializationNumber1" type="GenericADM:tHexa" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="sourceIdentifierNumber2" type="GenericADM:tHexa" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="sequenceInitializationNumber2" type="GenericADM:tHexa" use="required"/>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tNvfb2Parameters">
		<xs:attribute name="id" type="rail:tGenericID" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="nvfb2SourceAddress" type="xs:integer" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="nvfb2DestinationAddress" type="xs:integer" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="subnet" type="xs:integer" use="required"/>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tSntpParameters"/>
	<xs:complexType name="tSnmpParameters"/>
	<xs:complexType name="tEuroradioPlusParameters">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="emitterEuroEquipmentParameters" type="GenericADM:tEuroEquipmentParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="receiverEuroEquipmentParameters" type="GenericADM:tEuroEquipmentParameters"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="euroKeys" type="GenericADM:eEuroKeys"/>
		</xs:sequence>
		<xs:attribute name="id" type="rail:tGenericID" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute default="false" name="NTG_FI" type="xs:boolean" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Information about usage of NTG Functional Interface protocol layer. True means that the NTG FI layer is active.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="false" name="SCALABLE_ETCS" type="xs:boolean" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Information about usage of scalable ETCS_ID on this communication interface.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eEuroKeys">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="3" minOccurs="0" name="euroKey" type="GenericADM:tEuroKey"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tFsfb2Global">
		<xs:attribute name="ssrDelay" type="GenericADM:tUint32" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates for FSFB2 equipment, the maximum delay between a request (Sequence Start Enquiry) and its answer (Sequence Start Reply).</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="operation" type="xs:boolean" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates for FSFB2 equipment, if a Trigger message is to be sent to FSFB2 equipment</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="nbBsdToSsr" type="GenericADM:tUint16" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates for FSFB2 equipment, the number of BSD messages received before periodic realignment.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="maxSsrRetry" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates for FSFB2 equipment, the number of attemps to achieve periodic realignment.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="maxLifeTime" type="GenericADM:tUint32" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates the maximum time validity of the last message coming from equipment.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="maxError" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates for FSFB2 equipment, the tolerance in the BSD Sequence Counter verification.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="maxDeltaTC" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates for FSFB2 equipment, the allowed maximum number of consecutive lost Safety Data messages (with different Time Counters).</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="diagnosticFrameDeadline" type="GenericADM:tUint32" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates foreach FSFB2 equipment, the deadline for the Diagnostic Frame reception.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="applicationCategory" type="xs:string" use="optional"/>
		<xs:attribute name="tCycleTimer" type="GenericADM:tUint32" use="optional"/>
		<xs:attribute name="maxMissingMessages" type="GenericADM:tUint32" use="required"/>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tFsfb2Address">
		<xs:attribute name="fsfb2SourceAddress" type="xs:integer" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="bsdDestinationAddress" type="xs:integer" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="sseSsrDestinationAddress" type="xs:integer" use="required"/>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eDataVersionNumbers">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="2" minOccurs="1" name="dataVersionsNumber" type="GenericADM:tDataVersionsNumber"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tUevolParameters">
		<xs:attribute name="LOCAL_SSTY" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="LOCAL_SSID" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="LOCAL_LOGID" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="LOCAL_MSGID" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="REMOTE_SSTY" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="REMOTE_SSID" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="REMOTE_LOGID" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="REMOTE_MSGID" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="Application_Type" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required"/>
		<xs:attribute name="ITF_VER" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="optional"/>
		<xs:attribute name="GROUP_SSTY" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="optional"/>
		<xs:attribute name="GROUP_SSID" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="optional"/>
		<xs:attribute name="GROUP_LOGID" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="optional"/>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tSrttParameters">
		<xs:attribute name="srttUse" type="xs:boolean" use="optional"/>
		<xs:attribute name="srttTimeOut" type="GenericADM:tUint32" use="optional"/>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tEuroEquipmentParameters">
		<xs:attribute name="etcsIdValue" type="GenericADM:tUint24" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>the value of ETCS_ID</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="etcsIdType" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Identifies the kind of each connected peripheral.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="initiator" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates, for each peripheral, if the MSW is the Initiator (at Connection Management level) of the communication with this peripheral</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tSaiParameters">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="timers" type="GenericADM:tEuroTimers"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="delta" type="GenericADM:tEuroDelta"/>
		</xs:sequence>
		<xs:attribute name="saiProtocol" type="GenericADM:tEnumSaiProtocolType" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates the protocol used in SAI for message dating and sequencing.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="responseDelay" type="GenericADM:tInteger1_Unbounded" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates the maximum delay between a request and its answer. If this delay is reached, the connection is broken.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="maxMissingMessages" type="GenericADM:tInteger1_Unbounded" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates whatever the protocol, the allowed maximum number of consecutive lost messages.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="bigSizeMessageCRC" type="GenericADM:tEnumCRC" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicate the kind of CRC that has to be computed for long message</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tTleParameters">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="keepAwake" type="GenericADM:tKeepAwake"/>
		</xs:sequence>
		<xs:attribute name="qualityOfService" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates which Quality Of Service is required
0:A REDUNDANT SAMEQUALITY ONELINK
1:B REDUNDANT DIFFERENTQUALITY ONELINK
2:C NONREDUNDANT PRIMARYLINKONLY
3:D REDUNDANT SAMEQUALITY TWOLINKS
</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="maxDisconnectionDelay" type="GenericADM:tInteger1_Unbounded" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates the maximum delay allocated for the disconnection (TLE level).</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="maxConnectionDelay" type="GenericADM:tInteger1_Unbounded" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates the maximum delay allocated for the connection establishment (TLE level).</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="applicationType" type="GenericADM:tUint8" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Identifies the type of application embedded in this peripheral.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tEuroKey">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="4" minOccurs="1" name="serialNumber" type="GenericADM:tUint32"/>
		</xs:sequence>
		<xs:attribute name="key" type="GenericADM:tSlkab" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>The key is typed SL_KAB which  provides a String containing the KMAC key coded in HEX format respecting the following regular expression [0-9a-fA-F]{16}.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="startOfValidity" type="xs:dateTime" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Date that indicates the start of validity (inclusive) of the key</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="endOfValidity" type="xs:dateTime" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Date that indicates the end of validity (inclusive) of the key. (Default value to be confirmed if no limitation shall be set)</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="keyOrder" type="GenericADM:tEnumEurokeyOrder" use="required"/>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tEuroTimers">
		<xs:attribute name="tUpdateTimer" type="GenericADM:tUint32" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates whatever the protocol, the periodicity of the clock-offset update of this peripheral, ie. The maximum delay between 2 synchronisation procedures.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="tOffMax" type="GenericADM:tInteger1_Unbounded" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>This parameter is used to check the validity of the evaluated offset.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="tMax" type="GenericADM:tInteger1_Unbounded" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates the maximum transmission time of a message. If the transmission time is greater than T_MAX, the message is rejected.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="tExtraDelay" type="GenericADM:tUint32" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Optional delay added to T_MAX to define the maximum transmission time of a message.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="tCycleTimer" type="GenericADM:tUint32" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>This optional timer indicates the maximum delay between the receptions of two consecutive cyclic messages. If this delay is reached, the connection is broken.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tEuroDelta">
		<xs:attribute name="sameDeltaMax" type="GenericADM:tUint16" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Indicates the maximum number of cycles with the same delta. Once this maximum is reached, the communication must be synchronised again.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="maxAckRequest" type="GenericADM:tUint16" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Maximum number of retry of ACK request.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>

				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="junctionBoxType" type="GenericADM:tEnumJunctionBox" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Defines the type of junction boxes:
-	JunctionBox: used to connect cable between indoor and outdoor, or by installation team in cable length exceeds the cable strand
-	GAKBox : used to split the cable Quand when connecting a Quand to an equipment (e.g. Axle counter) and continue with other Quand to next equipment
-	DistributionBox: used to split distribute cables
</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>

</xs:documentation>

	<xs:complexType name="eServices">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="service" type="GenericADM:Service"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="Service">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="rail:tElementWithIDAndName">
				<xs:annotation>
					<xs:documentation>Service represents the complete set of RequestedTrainMovements that a given train must perform one after the other in order to satisfy the production of services scheduled by the RegulationElements. For example, it  consolidates the different RequestedTrainMovements from the beggining of the first movement up to the turnback on the other terminus.
		From the OCC Operator's point of view, a train is assigned a Service.</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="patternRefs" type="GenericADM:tPatternRefs">
						<xs:annotation>
							<xs:documentation>The list of patternRef which compose the service with patternRef being a reference to pattern ID</xs:documentation>
						</xs:annotation>
					</xs:element>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="insertionRefs" type="GenericADM:tInsertionRefs">
						<xs:annotation>
							<xs:documentation>The list of Insertion(s) which can be used for the service with Insertion being a reference to Insertion ID</xs:documentation>
						</xs:annotation>
					</xs:element>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="withdrawalRefs" type="GenericADM:tWithdrawalRefs">
						<xs:annotation>
							<xs:documentation>The list of Withdrawals  which can be used for the service with Withdrawal being a reference to Withdrawal ID</xs:documentation>
						</xs:annotation>
					</xs:element>
				</xs:sequence>
				<xs:attribute name="type" type="GenericADM:tEnumTypeService" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>The type of the service: "nominal" or "provisional"</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eInsertions">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="insertion" type="GenericADM:tInsertion"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tInsertion">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="rail:tElementWithIDAndName">
				<xs:annotation>
					<xs:documentation>Insertion defines the insertion that shall be used to insert train in a specific terminus platform of the nominal Service, automatically by the ATS.</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="patternRef" type="rail:tGenericRef"/>
				</xs:sequence>
				<xs:attribute name="priority" type="xs:integer" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Indicate the priority between several Insertions. The priority shall decrease from 1 to 10 (1 being the highest priority)</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eWithdrawals">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="withdrawal" type="GenericADM:tWithdrawal"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tWithdrawal">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="rail:tElementWithIDAndName">
				<xs:annotation>
					<xs:documentation>Withdrawal defines the withdrawal that shall be used to withdraw a train from a specific terminus platform of the nominal Service, automatically by the ATS.</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="patternRef" type="rail:tGenericRef"/>
				</xs:sequence>
				<xs:attribute name="priority" type="xs:integer" use="optional"/>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="ePatterns">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="pattern" type="GenericADM:tPattern"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tPattern">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="rail:tElementWithIDAndName">
				<xs:annotation>
					<xs:documentation>is a static set of PredefinedTrainMovements that has been defined during data preparation. It is part of a Service or a turnback and used to build on-line Trips.</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="elementaryPathRefs" type="GenericADM:tElementaryPathRefs"/>
				</xs:sequence>
				<xs:attribute name="type" type="GenericADM:tEnumTypePattern" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>The type of the pattern: passengerMovement, turnback, manoeuver</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="automaticTurnback" type="xs:boolean" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Define if the turnback is automatic or not. The possible values are:
False: no automatic turnback
True: automatic turnback</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eElementaryPaths">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="elementaryPath" type="GenericADM:tElementaryPath"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tElementaryPath">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="GenericADM:tGraphicalLogicalPath"/>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>

		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="patternRef" type="rail:tGenericRef"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tInsertionRefs">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="insertionRef" type="rail:tGenericRef"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tWithdrawalRefs">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="withdrawalRef" type="rail:tGenericRef"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tElementaryPathRefs">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="elementaryPathRef" type="rail:tGenericRef"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eDistancesFromReferencedInstallationElements">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="distanceFromReferencedInstallationElement" type="GenericADM:tDistanceFromReferencedInstallationElement"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tDistanceFromReferencedInstallationElement">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="GenericADM:tDistanceFromReferencedElement">
				<xs:attribute name="minInstallationTolerance" type="rail:tLengthM" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Min installation tolerance (e.g. if  minInstallationTolerance = 1 and  distanceFromReferencedInstallationElement = 50 m, the equipment shall be installated at least at 49 m from the referenced element</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="maxInstallationTolerance" type="rail:tLengthM" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Max installation tolerance (e.g. if  maxInstallationTolerance = 1 and  distanceFromReferencedInstallationElement = 50 m, the equipment shall be installated at less than 51 m from the referenced element</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eDistancesFromReferenceTrackSurveyElements">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="distanceFromReferencedTrackSurveyElement" type="GenericADM:tDistanceFromReferencedTrackSurveyElement"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tDistanceFromReferencedTrackSurveyElement">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="GenericADM:tDistanceFromReferencedElement"/>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eCableDuctTrackCrossings">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="cableDuctTrackCrossing" type="GenericADM:tCableDuctTrackCrossing"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tCableDuctTrackCrossing">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="rail:tBasePlacedElement"/>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eCableDuctTrackCrossingGroups">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="cableDuctTrackCrossingGroup" type="GenericADM:tCableDuctTrackCrossingGroup"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tCableDuctTrackCrossingGroup">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="GenericADM:tTrackCrossingElement">
				<xs:attribute name="type" type="xs:string" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Type of trackcrossing. This fied is not currently used but could be used in the future to distinguish different types of trackcrossings</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="length" type="rail:tLengthM" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Length of the track crossing</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="eCables">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="cable" type="GenericADM:tCable"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tCable">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="rail:tElementWithIDAndName">
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="passesByRefs" type="GenericADM:ePassesByRefs">
						<xs:annotation>
							<xs:documentation>List of ID of cableDuctTrackCrossing Group</xs:documentation>
						</xs:annotation>
					</xs:element>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="containedTrackCrossingByRefs" type="GenericADM:eContainedTrackCrossingByRefs">
						<xs:annotation>
							<xs:documentation>List of the Ids of the cableDuctTrackCrossing</xs:documentation>
						</xs:annotation>
					</xs:element>
				</xs:sequence>
				<xs:attribute name="connectedObjectRef" type="rail:tGenericRef" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>ID of the object connected to the end extremity of the cable,  which is either a  punctual object, an EquipmentRoom or a Junction Box</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="connectedObjectType" type="xs:string" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Type of the object corresponding to the end extremity of the cable</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="connectedCenterRef" type="rail:tGenericRef" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>ID of the object connected to the start extremity of the cable,  which is either an Equipment Room or a Junction Box</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="connectedCenterType" type="xs:string" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Type of the object which is either an EquipmentRoom or a Junction Box</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="length" type="rail:tLengthM" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>length of the cable</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="increaseRate" type="GenericADM:tPercentage" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>The increase rate field allows user to define supplementary cable length that is taken in account when computing cables length</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="environment" type="GenericADM:tEnumEnvironment" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Define if the cable in underground or overground</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="cableType" type="xs:string" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Type of Cable</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>

						<xs:annotation>
							<xs:documentation>Define all the parameter of the Protocol which are specific for a connection</xs:documentation>
						</xs:annotation>
					</xs:element>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="0" name="applicationRefs" type="GenericADM:tApplicationRef"/>
				</xs:sequence>
				<xs:attribute name="connectionTypeDefinitionRef" type="rail:tGenericRef" use="required"/>
				<xs:attribute name="direction" type="GenericADM:tConnectionDirection" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Direction of the connection</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="redundantConnection" type="xs:boolean" use="required"/>
				<xs:attribute default="External" name="COM_ITF_TYPE" type="GenericADM:tEnumCOM_ITF_TYPE" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Define the type of the communication interface</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute default="0" name="COM_ITF_PRIO" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_63" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Define the priority of the communication interface DSCP in the IP header for this communication interface. Default value is 0 generally considered by networkforroutine or best effort communications.</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute default="Autonomous" name="COM_ITF_TRIGGER_MODE" type="GenericADM:tEnumCOM_ITF_TRIGGER_MODE" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Define if communication interface is autonomous (configuration fixed) or triggered (configuration dynamically learned when message received). For triggered communication interface, only identification parameters of IP, UDP protocols are learned from input messages.</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute default="NonFiltered" name="COM_ITF_INPUT_FILTERING" type="GenericADM:tEnumCOM_ITF_INPUT_FILTERING" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Define if input message are filtered or not. In case of a communication interface which is defined as filtered then only the last message received on the communication interface is transmitted to the application. Else all messages received during last cycle are transmitted to the application. Parameter shall be set to NonFiltered or not defined for all communication interfaces based on TCP.</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>

					<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
					The S0 operational configuration corresponds to:
					- Use of Standard commands
					- Use of a hardware variant including 8 SM outputs: SM2, SM5 or SM7.
					- No specific restriction on Signal connection
					- Red Retaining function is not activated.
					This is an emulation of Standard SM Module.
				</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
			</xs:enumeration>
			<xs:enumeration value="S1">
				<xs:annotation>
					<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
					The S1 operational configuration corresponds to:
					- Use of Basic commands
					- Use of a hardware variant including 8 SM outputs with red-retaining: SM2 or SM7.
					- Outputs 7 and 8 shall be restrictive lamps.
					- Red Retaining function is activated.
				</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
			</xs:enumeration>
			<xs:enumeration value="S2">
				<xs:annotation>
					<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
					The S2 operational configuration corresponds to:
					- Use of A_SIGNALS_COMMAND_S1_S2
					- Use of Basic commands
					- Use of a hardware variant including 8 SM outputs: SM2, SM5 or SM7.
					- No specific restriction on signal connection.
					- Red Retaining function is not activated.
					
				</xs:documentation>
				</xs:annotation>
			</xs:enumeration>
		</xs:restriction>
	</xs:simpleType>

				</xs:sequence>
				<xs:attribute name="FREEZING_TIMER_0_TO_1" type="xs:unsignedByte" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Freezing timer 0 to 1 applied on logical inputs. If set to 0, freezing functionality is disabled.

Each unit is corresponding to a freeze of 50 ms. For instance, a FREEZING_TIMER_0_TO_1 set to 5 will lead to a freeze during 250 ms

Freezing timer functionality is managed by STEPPER modules only. Consequently, even if this value is set to something else than 0, it won't freeze the value of the logical input for a guest module</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="FREEZING_TIMER_1_TO_0" type="xs:unsignedByte" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Freezing timer 1 to 0 applied on logical inputs. If set to 0, freezing functionality is disabled.

Each unit is corresponding to a freeze of 50 ms. For instance, a FREEZING_TIMER_1_TO_0 set to 5 will lead to a freeze during 250 ms

Freezing timer functionality is managed by STEPPER modules only. Consequently, even if this value is set to something else than 0, it won't freeze the value of the logical input for a guest module</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute fixed="true" name="INT_BUS_PRIO_IMPROVEMENT" type="GenericADM:tBoolean" use="optional">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Boolean used to define if the Input Module applies the new strategy for the management of TX messages priority on the internal bus, or if it applies the legacy strategy.

This attribute shall be left undefined or set to FALSE in case of IM111 or in case case of IM112 loaded with a software whose version is earlier to version 2.9.1.

This attribute shall be set to TRUE in case of IM112 loaded with software version 2.9.1 or later </xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>

	<xs:complexType name="tSM5BoardParameterSet">
		<xs:complexContent>
			<xs:extension base="GenericADM:tBoardParameterSet">
				<xs:sequence>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="SM5BoardAppliParameter" type="GenericADM:tSM5BoardAppliParameter"/>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="SM5BoardProdParameter" type="GenericADM:tSM5BoardProdParameter"/>
					<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="SM5BoardRedundancy" type="GenericADM:tSM5BoardRedundancy"/>
				</xs:sequence>
				<xs:attribute name="ZERO_CROSSING" type="GenericADM:tInteger1_3" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<constraint>
Typical values:
- for DC: 0
- for AC: 3
- for AC driving transformers: 2
						</constraint>
<category value="System"/></xs:appinfo>
						<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
For SM FPGA version before or equal to 1.1.0:
Zero crossing circuit activates and deactivates the outputs when the voltage waveforms makes the following transition at zero-phase:
- 0 (00): no synchronization. 
- 1 (01): transition from minus to plus 
- 2 (10): transition from plus to minus 
- 3 (11): transition dont care 

For SM FPGA starting from 1.2.0 (included):
Zero crossing activation, deactivation  configuration mode for the cell specified by index i
Each zero cross state is coded on two bits :
- 0 (00) or 1 (01): no synchronization.
- 2 (10) : activation at maximal voltage, deactivation on output current transition.
- 3 (11) : activation on voltage transition, deactivation on output current transition.

In case of PS_TYPE set to DC, the parameter ZERO_CROSSING is not taken into account but set to 0 by the dataprep compiler
					</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
				<xs:attribute name="OPERATIONAL_CONFIG" type="GenericADM:tEnumOperationalConfig" use="required">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="-"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="System"/></xs:appinfo>
						<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
						Define the operational configuration as identified in 5 of SyRSAD SM (A441469)
						</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
				</xs:attribute>
			</xs:extension>
		</xs:complexContent>
	</xs:complexType>

<unit value="-"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/>
<constraint> Current safety case covers only AC (2) </constraint></xs:appinfo>
