			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="PS_FREQ" type="GenericADM:tEnumPsFreq" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="Hz"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/>
<constraint> To be set to 0 in case of DC. </constraint></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">Frequency of the Trackside Power Supply (in Hz) </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="NIGHT_DIMMING" type="GenericADM:tBoolean" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="-"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
               Boolean flag to indicate if night dimming is enabled or not.
               -false : Night Dimming is disabled
               -true: Night Dimming is enabled;
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="PS_VALUE_DAY" type="GenericADM:tInteger0_240" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="Vrms"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/>
<constraint> PS_VALUE_DAY > 48
                            PS_VALUE_DAY*(1+PS_UPPER_TOL/100)*K_VMS_RMS_MAX_OK/100 lower than 253V
                    </constraint></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                Value of the Trackside Power Supply.
                Value used in "Day" if NIGHT_DIMMING is activated.
                This field must be set even if night dimming is deactivated (i.e. the "Day" values are always used by convention)
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="PS_VALUE_NIGHT" type="GenericADM:tInteger0_240" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="Vrms"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/>
<constraint> PS_VALUE_NIGHT > 48
                            PS_VALUE_NIGHT lower than PS_VALUE_DAY
                            PS_VALUE_DAY*(1-PS_LOWER_TOL/100)*K_VMS_RMS_MIN_OK/100 higher than PS_VALUE_NIGHT*(1+PS_UPPER_TOL/100)*K_VMS_RMS_MAX_OK/100 
                    </constraint></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                   Value of the Trackside Power Supply in "Night" supply mode.
                   Optional if the night dimming is inactive. Note : In this case, SM Guest Modules uses by convention the "Day" values.
                   Mandatory if the night dimming is active.
                   See NIGHT_DIMMING parameter.
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="PS_LOWER_TOL" type="GenericADM:tInteger0_50" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">Lower Tolerance of the Power Supply.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="PS_UPPER_TOL" type="GenericADM:tInteger0_50" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">Upper Tolerance of the Power Supply.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="DELAY_BEFORE_SEND_BACK_STATUS_TO_SC" type="GenericADM:tInteger0_10000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Delay that the SM Guest Module waits before sending back lamp state value to SC.
This delay is applyed only in case of change of SC command when no fault is present. 
This delay is not applied when a fault is present.
The attribute DELAY_BEFORE_SEND_BACK_STATUS_TO_SC defines a freezing time on logical outputs of SM objects of type OneBitSetting_STD and OneBitSetting_BASIC. 
This filtering will be used to avoid, in case of broken lamp, that was commanded to OFF and that is now becomes commanded to ON or FLASHING, a too early diagnostic reporting temporarily and wrongly a LIGHTEN value (instead of NOT_LIGHTEN as lamp is broken). This happens because the SM considers the lamp as OK (by default) and needs time to discover that it is broken. 
If this scenario has to be avoided (because of undesired behavior of the consumer of this information), DELAY_BEFORE_SEND_BACK_STATUS_TO_SC has to be set to a value big enough to let time for lamp proving to conclude on the real status of the lamp.
Notes: 
- This filtering is only applied when no fault is detected on the SM and when the IXL command changes. In all other cases, DELAY_BEFORE_SEND_BACK_STATUS_TO_SC filtering is not used.
- A bigger value of DELAY_BEFORE_SEND_BACK_STATUS_TO_SC means slower reporting to the IXL in case of command change.
For steady ON command
DELAY_BEFORE_SEND_BACK_STATUS_TO_SC 
      > (2*50 ms + OFF_ON_LP_FILT_TIM_MAX + MAX_FAULT_ON_LAMP * 50 ms) 
         [* 90/50]
where the optional factor 90/50? has to be used if, instead of typical times (NRT), Safe Response Time (SRT) confidence is required. 90 ms comes from (number of watchdog cycles + 1) * 5 ms? and 50 ms is the nominal task cycle implementing the SM function.
For FLASHING command
An additional value has to be added to the right term of the inequality in case of flashing which is up to
MaxFaultOnLamp * maximum among all the FLASHING_PERIOD associated to the cells of the LRU
      See A464154 for more precise value
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tSM5BoardProdParameter">
		<xs:sequence>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="MS" type="GenericADM:tMS"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="VA_VB_VOUT" type="GenericADM:tVA_VB_VOUT"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="CURRENT" type="GenericADM:tCURRENT"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="OUT_FLT_MGT" type="GenericADM:tOUT_FLT_MGT"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="CELL_MGT" type="GenericADM:tCELL_MGT"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="LAMP_MGT" type="GenericADM:tLAMP_MGT"/>
			<xs:element maxOccurs="1" minOccurs="1" name="FLASHING_TIMERS" type="GenericADM:tFLASHING_TIMERS"/>
		</xs:sequence>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tSM5BoardRedundancy">
		<xs:attribute name="TO_ACTIVE_AND_OTHER_NOT_PRESENT" type="GenericADM:tInteger0_2000">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="User"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Timer used to detect absence of "Active" while system is operational
Typical value is 300 ms.
The time used during election (TO_ActiveAndOtherNotPresentDuringElection) will be set to twice the value of TO_ActiveAndOtherNotPresent.
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="TO_AVOID_PING_PONG" type="GenericADM:tInteger0">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="User"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
This parameter is the initial value (value taken after power on) of TO_AvoidPingPong.
This value has to be bigger than the time required to perform self-tests of the board while it is in "Standby" mode.
The value shall be a multiple of 50 ms
Special values:
    - 0: immediately elapsed
    - (0x51EB851+1) .. 0xFFFFFFFD: values truncated internally to 0xFFFFFFFD
    - 0xFFFFFFFE: forbidden (cannot be used as infinite may be used only once)
    - 0xFFFFFFFF: forbidden (N/A as an initial value)
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="TO_PROTECTION" type="GenericADM:tInteger0">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="User"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
This parameter is the initial value (value taken after power on) of TO_Protection.
Initial value of "TO_Protection"
The value shall be a multiple of 50 ms
Special values:
    - 0: immediately elapsed
    - (0x51EB851+1) .. 0xFFFFFFFD: values truncated internally to 0xFFFFFFFD
    - 0xFFFFFFFE: forbidden (cannot be used as infinite may be used only once)
    - 0xFFFFFFFF: forbidden (N/A as an initial value)
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="REDUNDANCY_STATUS_BIT_FILTERING_TIME" type="GenericADM:tInteger0_2000">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="User"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
The attribute REDUNDANCY_STATUS_BIT_FILTERING_TIME defines the time after which a new ACTIVE board will set its active bit to 1. This parameter shall be bigger than the time needed to prove the lamp, i.e. :

(550 ms + OFF_ON_LP_FILT_TIM_MAX + 50 * MAX_FAULT_ON_LAMP) [* 90/50]
where the optional factor 90/50? has to be used if, instead of typical times (NRT), Safe Response Time (SRT) confidence is required. 90 ms comes from (number of watchdog cycles + 1) * 5 ms? and 50 ms is the nominal task cycle implementing the SM function.

For FLASHING command
An additional value has to be added to the right term of the inequality in case of flashing which is up to
MaxFaultOnLamp * maximum among all the FLASHING_PERIOD associated to the cells of the LRU
      See A464154 for more precise value
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tMS">
		<xs:attribute name="VMS_RMS_KMIN_AC" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_100" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<recommended level="high" value="0"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Scale factor between RMS value and minimum allowable average value of the Master Switch output voltage in the case of AC power supply. 

                            This parameter is used to detect abnormal offset on AC voltage.
                            If trackside power supply does not meet the criteria after filtering of transients, the master-switch will be opened.
                    </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="VMS_RMS_KMAX_AC" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_150" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<recommended value="10"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                           Scale factor between RMS value and maximum allowable average value of the Master Switch output voltage in the case of AC power supply.
                           This parameter is used to detect abnormal offset on AC voltage.
                           If trackside power supply does not meet the criteria after filtering of transients, the master-switch will be opened.
                    </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="VMS_RMS_KMAX_DC" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_150" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<recommended value="120"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">Scale factor between RMS value and maximum allowable average value of the Master Switch output voltage in the case of DC power supply.
This parameter is used to detect that DC power supply is not AC.
If trackside power supply does not meet the criteria after filtering of transients, the master-switch will be opened.
                    </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="VMS_RMS_KMIN_DC" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_100" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<recommended value="80"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Scale factor between RMS value and minimum allowable average value of the Master Switch output voltage in the case of DC power supply.
This parameter is used to detect that DC power supply is not AC.
If trackside power supply does not meet the criteria after filtering of transients, the master-switch will be opened.
					</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="K_VMS_RMS_MIN_OK" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_100" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<recommended value="95"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Factor  used to determine the minimum threshold of the Master Switch output supply voltage. Used for both Day? and "Night" supply modes.
Threshold = K_VMS_RMS_MIN_OK * MIN_VMS where MIN_VMS is the nominal value PS_VALUE_DAY or PS_VALUE_NIGHT including the effect PS_LOWER_TOL.
This check is used to define the minimum acceptable input voltage.
If trackside power supply does not meet the criteria after filtering of transients and if OUTPUTS_INHIBITION has been set to true, the outputs will be inhibited.
Note: If trackside power supply provides, for a certain time, a voltage above the configured missing threshold but too low to avoid MOS leakage (example : 25 VAC), Master switch will be opened.?
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="K_VMS_RMS_MAX_OK" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_150" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<recommended value="105"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Factor used to determine the maximum threshold of the Master Switch output supply voltage.
Used for both Day? and "Night" supply modes. See constraints on PS_VALUE_DAY and PS_VALUE_NIGHT.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="K_VMS_PERIOD_MIN" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_100" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<recommended value="96"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Factor (kmin) used to determine the minimum threshold of the period of the trackside power supply.
VmsPeriodMin = K_VMS_PERIOD_MIN * 1/PS_FREQ
In case of frequency too low, the effect is the opening of master-switch (as an incorrect frequency may induce wrong measurements).
If more than 4 percents of tolerance is configured and if frequency changes more than 4 %, there could be undue failure detected (cell error type 3, 4 or 5). This is due to discrepancy of measures between channels due to the fact that the macro measures are no more aligned on the trackside power supply frequency.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="K_VMS_PERIOD_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_150" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<recommended value="104"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Factor used to determine the maximum threshold of the period of the trackside power supply.
VmsPeriodMax = K_VMS_PERIOD_MAX * 1/PS_FREQ 
In case of frequency too high, the effect is the opening of master-switch (as an incorrect frequency may induce wrong measurements).
If more than 4 percents of tolerance is configured and if frequency changes more than 4 %, there could be undue failure detected (cell error type 3, 4 or 5). This is due to discrepancy of measures between channels due to the fact that the macro measures are no more aligned on the trackside power supply frequency.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="MAX_FAULT_IND_RELAY_TEST" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_5" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="-"/>
<constraint>This parameter must be forced to 3 (fixed).</constraint>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">Maximum acceptable number of faults observed on individual test of each relay of the Master Switch</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="K_VMS_RMS_MISSING_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_100" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<recommended value="10"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="Product"/>
<constraint> VmsRmsMissingMax = K_VMS_RMS_MISSING_MAX * MIN(PS_DAY,PS_NIGHT).
VmsRmsMissingMax shall be lower than VoutLeakageMax (see GAIN_VOUT_LEAKAGE_MAX)
In case of SM in redundancy using transformers, it is advised to have VmsRmsMissingMax bigger than 
   8 * 2% of MAX(PS_VALUE_DAY,PS_VALUE_NIGHT). This to avoid a MIB failure code related to cell error when entering in "NOT_AVAILABLE" (SM out of order).
                                </constraint></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                        Factor used to determine the threshold below which output supply voltage is considered as "MISSING".
                        VmsRmsMissingMax = K_VMS_RMS_MISSING_MAX * MIN(PS_DAY,PS_NIGHT).
                        In case of missing power supply, the outputs are inhibited.

                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="MAX_CURRENT_MS" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_70" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="100mA"/>
<recommended value="60"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Maximum tolerable threshold above which it is detected that over-current is flowing through the Master Switch.
                            Physical limit is 6A (Value 60) but user can decide to open master-switch in case of lower value if this situation is considered as abnormal.
                            In anycase, 6A shall be the maximum value.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="MIN_OK_ON_MAX_CURRENT_MS" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50 ms"/>
<recommended value="2"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">Minimum required limit of counter of no faults of check on sum of currents (MAX_CURRENT_MS) </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="MAX_FAULT_ON_MAX_CURRENT_MS" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50 ms"/>
<recommended value="4"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en"> Maximum tolerable limit of counter of faults on check of max sum of currents (MAX_CURRENT_MS)
                                 Increasing this value will allow a longer in-rush (higher than MAX_CURRENT_MS) before Master-Switch opening.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tVA_VB_VOUT">
		<xs:attribute name="OFFSET_DELTA_VA_VMS_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="V"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 5 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">Offset used to compute maximum allowable voltage deviation between VMS and Va_i, see also GAIN_DELTA_VA_VMS_MAX. </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="GAIN_DELTA_VA_VMS_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 2 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Gain used to compute maximum allowable voltage deviation between VMS and Va_i.
                            The maximum voltage deviation between VMS and Va_i is given by the formula 
                            DeltaVaVmsMax = OFFSET_DELTA_VA_VMS_MAX + (GAIN_DELTA_VA_VMS_MAX / 100) * PS_VALUE_DAY
                            The comparison is performed each time the MOS is expected to be OFF and allow to detect a MOS leakage.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="OFFSET_DELTA_VB_VMS_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="V"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 5 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Offset used to compute maximum allowable voltage deviation between VMS and Vb_i, see also GAIN_DELTA_VB_VMS_MAX. 
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="GAIN_DELTA_VB_VMS_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 2 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Gain used to compute maximum allowable voltage deviation between VMS and Vb_i.
                            The maximum voltage deviation between VMS and Vb_i is given by the formula 
                            DeltaVbVmsMax = OFFSET_DELTA_VB_VMS_MAX + (GAIN_DELTA_VB_VMS_MAX / 100) * PS_VALUE_DAY
                            The comparison is performed each time the Relay is expected to be OPEN and allow to detect a leakage of branch relay.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="OFFSET_VOUT_LEAKAGE_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_20" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="V"/>
<constraint>
                                This value shall be set to 5 (forced) when SM is not in redundancy. 
                                When in redundancy, see constraint linked to VmsRmsMissingMax.
                                </constraint>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Offset used to compute threshold of maximum acceptable rms voltage on the terminals of a non-activated output, see also GAIN_VOUT_LEAKAGE_MAX
                            VoutLeakageMax shall be higher than VmsRmsMissingMax.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="GAIN_VOUT_LEAKAGE_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_20" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<constraint>
                                This value shall be set to 10 (forced) when SM is not in redundancy. 
                                When in redundancy, see constraint linked to VmsRmsMissingMax.
                                </constraint>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Gain used to compute threshold of maximum acceptable rms voltage on the terminals of a non-activated output
                            The threshold value is given by :
                            VoutLeakageMax = OFFSET_VOUT_LEAKAGE_MAX + (GAIN_VOUT_LEAKAGE_MAX / 100) * PS_VALUE_DAY
                            This is used to detect type 2 errors (undue voltage and current)
                            VoutLeakageMax shall be higher than VmsRmsMissingMax
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="5" name="OFFSET_DELTA_VOUT_VMS_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="V"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 5 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Offset used to compute maximum allowable voltage deviation between Vms and VOut_i, due to cutoff components, see also GAIN_DELTA_VOUT_VMS_MAX.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="2" name="GAIN_DELTA_VOUT_VMS_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 2 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                        Gain used to compute maximum allowable voltage deviation between Vms and Vout_i, due to cutoff components.
                        The threshold is given by the formula:
                        DeltaVoutVmsMax equal OFFSET_DELTA_VOUT_VMS_MAX + (GAIN_DELTA_VOUT_VMS_MAX / 100) * PS_VALUE_DAY
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tCURRENT">
		<xs:attribute name="LEAKAGE_CURRENT_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedShort0_50" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="mA"/>
<recommended value="20"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Maximum tolerable leakage current for a not activated output, this is used to detect type 2 errors.
                            Recommended value is 20mA.
                            In some specific condition (long cable and high crosstalk condition) this value has to be increased.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tOUT_FLT_MGT">
		<xs:attribute name="MAX_FORCE_CTL_OK_TIM" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedShort0_1000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<recommended value="150"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="System"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                                    Maximum duration of lamp fault detection filtering after the end of transient or missing supply.
                                    This to allow the power supply establishement before declaring lamp or cell fault.      
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="MAX_PWS_CTL_OK_TIM" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedShort0_15000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<recommended value="500"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="System"/>
<constraint> MAX_PWS_CTL_OK_TIM = MAX_PWS_TRANSIENT_TIM</constraint></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                                       Maximum duration of outputs control loss mask after a transient or absence of power supply.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="MAX_PWS_TRANSIENT_TIM" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedShort50_15000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<recommended value="500"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="System"/>
<constraint> MAX_PWS_CTL_OK_TIM = MAX_PWS_TRANSIENT_TIM </constraint></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Maximum time during which output controls are inhibited when there is a temporary interruption in electrical power supply during power network switching.
                            After this time, the controls apply and can detect voltage fault, except when the power supply is missing (see K_VMS_RMS_MISSING_MAX) in this case, the transient is considered permanently and appropriate alarm is produced.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="MAX_PS_TRANSIENTS" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedShort0_200" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<recommended value="20"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="System"/>
<constraint> MAX_PS_TRANSIENTS > MIN_PS_TRANSIENTS 
                                             Function-TBD(MAX_PWS_TRANSIENT_TIM,MAX_PWS_CTL_OK_TIM,MAX_FORCE_CTL_OK_TIM)
                                </constraint></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                        Threshold used to detect appearance of undue transients on trackside power. 
                        One test is done every software cycle (typically 50 ms)
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="MIN_PS_TRANSIENTS" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedShort0_200" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<recommended value="5"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="System"/>
<constraint> MAX_PS_TRANSIENTS > MIN_PS_TRANSIENTS 
                                             Function-TBD(MAX_PWS_TRANSIENT_TIM,MAX_PWS_CTL_OK_TIM,MAX_FORCE_CTL_OK_TIM)
                                </constraint></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                        Threshold used to detect disappearance of undue transients on trackside power. 
                        One test is done every software cycle (typically 50 ms). 
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="TEMP_EXC_VMS_TIM_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedShort0_1000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<recommended value="3000"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Time of master-switch temporary opening  following a frequency control fault 
                            (ie frequency of trackside power supply does not meet the criteria imposed by 
                            K_VMS_PERIOD_MAX and K_VMS_PERIOD_MIN)
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="TEMP_VMS_VOLT_FAULT_TIM_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedShort0_1000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<recommended value="3000"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                             Time of master-switch temporary opening  following an output volt fault.
                            (ie when value of trackside power supply does not meet the criteria imposed by K_VMS_RMS_MAX_OK and K_VMS_RMS_MIN_OK)
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="3" name="CNT_EXC_VMS_FREQ_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="-"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 3 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Maximum master switch closure retries in case of frequency control fault.
                            (ie frequency of trackside power supply does not meet the criteria imposed by 
                            K_VMS_PERIOD_MAX and K_VMS_PERIOD_MIN)
                            If this value is reached, then Master Switch is definitively opened.
                            
                            In case of SM used in redundancy...
                            If the configuration parameter CNT_EXC_VMS_FREQ_MAX is set to 0, when the frequency becomes out of range, 
                            the "Active bit" will change to 0 after that the lamp state has already changed to NOT_LIGHTEN. 
                            This will cause NOT_LIGHTEN to be voted by COM-X and to be sent to IXL (availability/performance issue).
                            So, when SM is in redundancy, this parameter has not be 0.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="4" name="CNT_NO_EXC_VMS_FREQ_MIN" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 4 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Number of applicative cycles used to forget the number of occurrences of frequency control fault.
                            (ie frequency of trackside power supply does not meet the criteria imposed by 
                            K_VMS_PERIOD_MAX and K_VMS_PERIOD_MIN)
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="3" name="CNT_VMS_VOLT_FAULT_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte1_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="-"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 3 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Maximum master switch closure retries in case of output volt fault.
                            (ie when value of trackside power supply does not meet the criteria imposed by K_VMS_RMS_MAX_OK and K_VMS_RMS_MIN_OK)
                            If this value is reached, then Master Switch is definitely opened.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="4" name="CNT_NO_VMS_VOLT_FAULT_MIN" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 4 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Number of applicative cycles used to forget the number of occurence of output volt fault.
                             (ie when value of trackside power supply does not meet the criteria imposed by K_VMS_RMS_MAX_OK and K_VMS_RMS_MIN_OK)
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="2" name="MAX_FAULT_VMS" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 2 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Maximum tolerable limit of applicative cycles to have fault on VMS divergence control.
                           (definitive opening of Master-Switch)
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="4" name="MIN_OK_VMS" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 4 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Time to forget any VMS divergence fault.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="2" name="MAX_FAULT_VMS_FREQ" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 2 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                           Maximum tolerable limit of applicative cycle to have fault on VMS frequency divergence control.
                           (definitive opening of Master-Switch)
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="4" name="MIN_OK_VMS_FREQ" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 4 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Time to forget any VMS frequency divergence fault.  
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="true" name="OUTPUTS_INHIBITION" type="GenericADM:tBoolean" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="-"/>
<constraint>This parameter shall be set to "TRUE" (fixed).</constraint>
<category value="System"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Boolean used to parameterize the way to inhibit the outputs in case of degraded mode of power supply : The output supply is wrong (ie not in range defined by K_VMS_RMS_MAX_OK and K_VMS_RMS_MIN_OK) but it is not missing (according to K_VMS_RMS_MISSING_MAX)
- When sets to TRUE: if a degraded mode of the output supply voltage is detected, all SM outputs are inhibited,
- When sets to FALSE: if a degraded mode of the output supply voltage is detected, inhibition of SM outputs is not requested.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tCELL_MGT">
		<xs:attribute name="VOLT_OFF_ON_FILT_TIM_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedShort0_500" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<recommended value="150"/>
<category value="System"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Filtering time for cell error after an output is just switched ON.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="VOLT_ON_OFF_FILT_TIM_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedShort0_500" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<recommended value="150"/>
<category value="System"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Filtering time for cell error after an output is just switched OFF.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="TEMP_INHIB_TYPE_1_TIM_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedShort0_1000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<recommended value="3000"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Time of temporary master switch opening after type 1 failure is detected.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="TEMP_INHIB_TYPE_2_TIM_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedShort0_1000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<recommended value="3000"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Time of temporary master switch opening after type 2 failure is detected.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="2" name="CNT_INHIB_TYPE_1_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="-"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 2 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Number of retries of Master-switch closure after type 1 failure is detected.                            
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="4" name="CNT_NO_FAULT_TYPE_1_MIN" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 4 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Time in number of applicative cycle to forget type 1 fault after a master-switch closure.           
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="2" name="CNT_INHIB_TYPE_2_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="-"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 2 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Number of retries of Master-switch closure after type 2 failure is detected.                            
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="4" name="CNT_NO_FAULT_TYPE_2_MIN" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 4 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Time in number of applicative cycles to forget type 2 fault after a master-switch closure.          
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="6" name="MAX_FAULT_A" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 6 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Time to declare a type 3 fault (output current divergence)
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="4" name="MIN_OK_A" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 4 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Time to forget a type 3 fault (output current divergence)
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="6" name="MAX_FAULT_PACT" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 6 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Time to declare a type 4 fault (active power divergence)    
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="4" name="MIN_OK_PACT" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 4 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Time to forget a type 4 fault (active power divergence)
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="2" name="MAX_FAULT_Vx" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 2 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                            Time to declare a type 5 fault (voltage divergence) 
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute fixed="4" name="MIN_OK_Vx" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<constraint>This value shall be set to 4 (forced)</constraint>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="Product"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en"> 
                            Time to forget a type 5 fault (voltage divergence)  
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="REGRADATION_FILTERING_TIME" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedInt0_10000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<recommended value="6100"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="Product"/>
<constraint> 
                                REGRADATION_FILTERING_TIME >(MIN_OK_LAMP+2)*CELL_FLASHING_PERIOD + 50 
                                and
                                REGRADATION_FILTERING_TIME > OFF_ON_LP_FILT_TIM_MAX.
                                The CELL_FLASHING_PERIOD to be used in this formula is the biggest value of the flashing period among all cells of the considered LRU
                                In case flashing is not used, CELL_FLASHING_PERIOD has to be considered at 50 ms.
                                </constraint></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Maximum time let to see that a lamp has been repaired.
This parameter is used in the XTalk management.
REGRADATION_FILTERING_TIME has to be big enough to let the lamp proving detect a repair of the lamp (see constraint)
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="TIME_BEFORE_DECLARING_UNDUE_VOUT" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedInt0_10000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<recommended value="6200"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="Product"/>
<constraint> 
                              TIME_BEFORE_DECLARING_UNDUE_VOUT > (MAX(MIN_OK_LAMP;MAX_FAULT_ON_LAMP)*CELL_FLASHING_PERIOD+100) 
                              and
                              TIME_BEFORE_DECLARING_UNDUE_VOUT >REGRADATION_FILTERING_TIME+50
                              In case flashing is not used, CELL_FLASHING_PERIOD has to be considered at 50 ms.
                                </constraint></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Delay before raising Type 2 errors on cells. (Xtalk) 
See constraint.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="TIME_BEFORE_NEW_REGRAD_ATTEMPT" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedInt0_600000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<recommended value="60000"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="Product"/>
<constraint> shall be higher than 60000 (=1 minute) to not exceed the rated number of operation of the relay considering lamp broken during 20 years </constraint></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Time before a new regradation attempt (after lamp failure detection)
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="MIN_OK_CONTINUOUS_VA_VB_TEST" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_50">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>
                            Minimum required number of "no faults" on Va/Vb checks of Cell i (checks performed outside self-tests of cells).
                            This parameter shall be set to 3 to avoid the cross talk effects described in atvcm00578001. 
                            Note: 3 comes from the minimum ON duration in flashing command (250 ms [= 5 applicative cycles] - margin).
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="MAX_FAULT_CONTINUOUS_VA_VB_TEST" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_50">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>
                            Maximum tolerable limit of counter of "faults" on Va/Vb checks of Cell i (checks performed outside self-tests of cells).
                            This parameter shall be set to a value greater than 3 to avoid effects due to the temporary problems explained in note of OC_SwRS_SM_0117. 
                            This parameter shall be set to a value greater than 25 to avoid the cross talk effects described in atvcm00578001.
                            This parameter shall not be too high to detect quickly the 4 failures case (see atvcm00728527)
                            Note: 25 comes from the maximum OFF duration in flashing command (1050 ms [= 21 applicative cycles] + margin).
                            Therefore, this parameter shall be set to 3 when SM is used in redundancy using transformers or to 25 in other cases.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tLAMP_MGT">
		<xs:attribute name="OFF_ON_LP_FILT_TIM_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedShort0_1000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<recommended value="250"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/>
<constraint> 
                              OFF_ON_LP_FILT_TIM_MAX lower (or equal) than (CELL_FLASHING_PERIOD*ON_RATIO/100-150)
                              CELL_FLASHING_PERIOD and ON_RATIO to be used in this formula are the values that provides the minimum duration of ON among all cells of the considered LRU
                                </constraint></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                              Filtering time for lamp proving after the associated output has been switched ON.
                              This timer is used to filter capacitive and inductive effect of cabling and loads.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="DAY_NIGHT_TRANSIENT_TIM_MAX" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedShort0_5000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<recommended value="2000"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                                 Filtering time for lamp proving (day/night incoherency only) after or before a transition of day/night flag.
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="MAX_FAULT_ON_LAMP" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<recommended value="2"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Time to confirm a lamp fault (open circuit or short-circuit) 
This is the number of 50ms cycles where output current and active power does not satisfy expected ranges (after a filtering time of OFF_ON_LP_FILT_TIM_MAX)
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="MIN_OK_LAMP" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_10" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="50ms"/>
<recommended value="4"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Time to reconsider positive lamp proving. 
This is the number of 50ms cycles where output current and active power satisfy again expected ranges (only used when a lamp fault has already been declared)
                            </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tFLASHING_TIMERS">
		<xs:attribute name="TIMER_ID" type="xs:string" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">Identifier of the timer (unique among XML file) This id will be used when declaring assiocated SM cells</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="FLASHING_PERIOD" type="GenericADM:tEnumIntFlashing" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="ms"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/>
<constraint>  Value shall be limited to the following list: 500/600/750/1000/1250/1500  </constraint></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">Period of the flashing output signal.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="ON_RATIO" type="GenericADM:tInteger25_75" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/>
<constraint>  
                                    If FLASHING_PERIOD=500  allowed value is 50%.
                                    If FLASHING_PERIOD=600  allowed value is 50%.
                                    If FLASHING_PERIOD=750  allowed values are 40% and 60%.
                                    If FLASHING_PERIOD=1000 allowed values are 25%,30%,35%,40%,45%,50%,55%,60%,65%,70%, and 75%.
                                    If FLASHING_PERIOD=1250 allowed values are 40% and 60%.
                                    If FLASHING_PERIOD=1500 allowed values are 30%,40%,50%,60% and 70%.
                        </constraint></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">ON ratio of the flashing signal (=Duty cycle)</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>

	<xs:complexType name="tSM5CellAppliParameter">
		<xs:attribute name="CURRENT_DAY" type="GenericADM:tInteger10_2000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="mA"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="User"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Nominal value of the current consumed by the output in Day? supply mode. 
Configurable by step of 1mA
This field must be set even if night dimming is deactivated (i.e. the "Day" values are always used by convention)
Note : Threshold for over current and current alarm are configured using this value and factors K_OVER_CURRENT and K_CURRENT_ALARM.
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="CURRENT_NIGHT" type="GenericADM:tInteger10_2000" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="mA"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="User"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                   Nominal value of the current consumed by the output in Night? supply mode. 
                   Configurable by step of 1mA.
                   Optional if the night dimming is inactive. Note : in this case, SM Guest Module uses by convention the "Day" values.
                   Mandatory if the night dimming is active.
                   See NIGHT_DIMMING parameter.
                   Note : Threshold for over current and current alarm are configured using this value and factors K_OVER_CURRENT and K_CURRENT_ALARM.
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="PACT_DAY" type="GenericADM:tInteger1000_150000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="mW"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="User"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Nominal value of the active power consumed by the corresponding output in Day? supply mode. 
Configurable by step of 100mW.
This field must be set even if night dimming is deactivated (i.e. the "Day" values are always used by convention)
Note : Thresholds are configured by using this value and K_ACT_PWR factor.
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="PACT_NIGHT" type="GenericADM:tInteger1000_150000" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="mW"/>
<safety impact="Yes"/>
<category value="User"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                Nominal value of the active power consumed by the output in Night? supply mode.
                Configurable by step of 100mW.
                Optional if the night dimming is inactive. 
                Note : In this case, SM Guest Module uses by convention the "Day" values.
                Mandatory if the night dimming is active.
                See NIGHT_DIMMING parameter.
                Note : Threshold are configured by using this value and K_ACT_PWR factor.
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="FLASHING_POLARITY" type="GenericADM:tEnumStrFlashing" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="N/A"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="User"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
            Polarity of the flashing
            The polarity could be :
            - NORMAL = flashing (ON state will light ON the lamp, OFF state will light OFF the lamp)
            - REVERSE = flashing (ON state will light OFF the lamp, OFF state will light ON the lamp)
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="USE_TIMER" type="xs:string" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="mA"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="User"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
                Identifier of the timer used to make this output flashing. 
                This has to be a reference to a timer defined in FLASHING_TIMERS.
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tSM5CellProdParameter">
		<xs:attribute name="K_ACT_PWR" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_100" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/>
<recommended value="80"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Factor used to determine the minimum active power threshold for output i. Used for both Day? and "Night" supply modes.
Lamp Proving Threshold in day = K_ACT_PWR * PACT_DAY. This value has to be greater or equal than 1W and less or equal than 150 W.
Lamp Proving Threshold in night = K_ACT_PWR * PACT_NIGHT. This value has to be greater or equal than 1W and less or equal than 150 W.
A load consuming an active power lower than this threshold will result in a lamp proving to 0.
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="K_CURRENT_ALARM" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte0_100" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/>
<recommended value="60"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">
Factor used to determine the alarm current threshold for output i.
Used for both Day? and "Night" supply modes.
Current alarm in day mode = K_CURRENT_ALARM * CURRENT_DAY.
Current alarm in night mode = K_CURRENT_ALARM * CURRENT_NIGHT.
Current alarm (day and night) shall be bigger than maximum leakage current (see LEAKAGE_CURRENT_MAX).
This threshold is used to set lamp alarm in the MIB, and do not impact the lamp proving mechanism based on active power.
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="K_OVER_CURRENT" type="GenericADM:tInteger100_10000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:appinfo>
<unit value="%"/>
<safety impact="No"/>
<category value="System"/>
<recommended value="200"/></xs:appinfo>
				<xs:documentation xml:lang="en">

Factor used to determine the over current threshold for output i. Used for both Day? and "Night" supply modes.
Threshold of over current in day mode = K_OVER_CURRENT * CURRENT_DAY. 
Threshold of over current in night mode = K_OVER_CURRENT * CURRENT_NIGHT.
In case in over current (short-circuit) the output is inhibited until next retry (TIME_BEFORE_NEW_REGRAD_ATTEMPT).
To inhibit this mechanism and rely on external fuses the maximum value can be used.
                </xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>

			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>"SubnetAddress" value shall be in the range [8000h, FFFEh].
Subnet is a unique identification of the subnet in the domain. It is used when messages are addressed to all nodes belonging to the Subnet (it can be seen as a multicast group). 
Note: the value FFFFh is reserved to broadcast.
</xs:documentation>

		<xs:attribute default="FullDuplex" name="UNP_DUPLEX_MODE_SCU4_EXT2" type="GenericADM:tETHERNET_DUPLEX_MODE_Type" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Duplex mode of external Ethernet port#2 of SCU4 in crossed links configuration: Half Duplex or Full duplex. Duplex mode if negotiated if speed parameter is 'AutoNegociation'</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="30" name="UNP_T_RECEPTION" type="xs:unsignedInt" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Time (in ms) to anticipate cycle timestamping of messages in the gateway in order to let enough time in channels to decode the message. . This time shall be carefully define using the performance model : It shall be defined according the maximum expected network load, a too short time will lead to divergences and this time directly impact the mean response time. This should be smaller than cycle duration</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="65000" name="UNP_MOON_PRIVATE_PORT_BASE" type="GenericADM:tInteger0_65000" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>UPDP port offset used for internal network management. This UDP port and following 535 ports are private port that shall not be in conflict with port used for external communication.Any message received by MooN on external network interface with one of these private UDP port may impact MooN availability.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="10.252.0.0" name="UNP_MOON_PRIVATE_IP_BASE" type="GenericADM:tUNP_MOON_PRIVATE_IP_BASE" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>IP address offset used for internal network management. This address has to be defined on 14 bits. It defines a private network that shall not be in conflict with external network. Any message received by MooN on external network interface with one private IP address may impact MooN availability. IP_BASE with 11.x.x.x are forbiden</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="English" name="UNP_DISPLAY_LANGUAGE" type="GenericADM:tUNP_DISPLAY_LANGUAGE" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Language used for MMI Display Man Machine Interface</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="50000" name="UNP_NTP_THRESHOLD" type="xs:unsignedInt" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Threshold defined in microsecond used for ntp synchronisation diagnostic</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>

Range between SCU1, SCU2, SCU3 and SCU4 are separeted so that when there is SCU redundancy switchover or Geographical redundancy handover, the sequence numbers value change from one range to another.</xs:documentation>

			<xs:annotation>

Incase of TCP, Total time for successive transitions will be T_CROSSED_LINKS_SWITCH + T_TCP_ MAXIMUM_RECONNECTION_TIME. Incase of TCP communication recommended value for T_TCP_ MAXIMUM_RECONNECTION_TIME = 5000</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tDTLS_CIPHER_SUITES">

			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Disable if it is required at system level</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="true" name="ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256_ENABLE" type="xs:boolean" use="optional">

			</xs:annotation>

		<xs:attribute default="true" name="ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384_ENABLE" type="xs:boolean" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>

			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="true" name="ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256_ENABLE" type="xs:boolean" use="optional">

	<xs:complexType name="tUNP_PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION">
		<xs:attribute name="UNP_SHORT_PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION" type="GenericADM:tUNP_SHORT_PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Version to identify the complete platform configuration (SW + DATA) version. This information is used used for software identification. It contains only a version information X.Y.Z.B which will also be used for SW package identification. (X, Y, Z, B as integerer between 0-99). This version is displayed on MMI at SCU start-up if parameter UNP_SHORT_PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION  is not defined.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="UNP_SHORT_PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION2" type="GenericADM:tUNP_SHORT_PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION2" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Short description to be displayed on MMI with safe signature (CRC32) at SCU start up.
Should be limited to 16 characters to be displayed on 1 line. If not defined the value displayed will be the version defined in UNP_SHORT_PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="UNP_LONG_PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION" type="GenericADM:tUNP_LONG_PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Long product description  to identify the complete platform configuration (SW + DATA). This information is not used on MooN platform.stored in configuration footprint  (255 ASCI car. Maximum)</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tUSP_EURORADIO_MOON_PARAMETERS">
		<xs:attribute default="0" name="SCALABLE_ETCS_ID_VALUE_MOON" type="GenericADM:tUint24" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Scalable ETCS ID of local MooN platform. When defined, this ETCS_ID value will be used for communication interfaces on which parameter SCALABLE_ETCS is set to True.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="NP_CHANNEL" name="ES_SEND_USED_CHANNEL" type="GenericADM:tEnumES_SEND_USED_CHANNEL" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Kind of channel on which the Emergency Stop message shall be sent.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="300" name="MOBILE_TIMEOUT_DURATION_HPU" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedInt5_600" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>At the end of timeout, if no input received on Euroradio connection, disconnection is launched. This timeout value is applicable for remote HPU (ETCS_ID_Type equal to ERTMS_PERIPHERAL).</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="20" name="NTG_RECONNECTION_TIMER" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedInt1_200" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>When using NTG FI layer, retry period for sending Trackside equipment identification request messages</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="40" name="MOBILE_TIMEOUT_DURATION_EVC" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedInt5_600" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>At the end of timeout, if no input received on Euroradio connection, disconnection is launched. This timeout value is applicable for remote EVC (ETCS_ID_Type equal to EVC)

Note: In the specific context of Scalable RBC, timeout is started when Master Request is send and it is stopped when a "Delete Euroradio session identifier" is made for corresponding ETCS_ID_Value</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="15" name="ALE_RECONNECTION_TIMER" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedInt1_150" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>When using NTG FI layer, retry period for sending ALE connection request messages. This timer is applicable when (MAX_CONNECTION_DELAY + MAX_DISCONNECTION_DELAY) timer has first elapsed.
Note: ALE connection request message will be sent after MAX_CONNECTION_DELAY + MAX_DISCONNECTION_DELAY + ALE_RECONNECTION_TIMER</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tUSP_GEO_REDUNDANCY">
		<xs:attribute default="1" name="T_ACK" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte1_10" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Maximum number of cycles to wait for GTM acknowledgement.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="1" name="T_GTM_CONTROL" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte1_10" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Maximum number of cycles to wait for GTM control.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="2" name="N_GTM_CONTROL" type="GenericADM:tUnsignedByte1_10" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Number of GTM_control messages to be sent to remote MooN.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
	<xs:complexType name="tUSP_TIMING">
		<xs:attribute name="USP_TCYCLE" type="GenericADM:tInteger100_1000" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Application cycle time in millisecond</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute default="0" name="USP_T_PRODUCTION" type="xs:unsignedInt" use="optional">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Time period  in millisecond to let free time for encoding last User Application messages. This parameter must be fine-tuned according to performance model as this directly impact time available for application. These values must be smaller than cycle time.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
		<xs:attribute name="USP_T_EDUCATION_MAX_DURATION" type="xs:unsignedInt" use="required">
			<xs:annotation>
				<xs:documentation>Time period to let free for education. This parameter must be fine-tuned according to performance model as this directly impact time available for application.  These values must be smaller than cycle time.</xs:documentation>
			</xs:annotation>
		</xs:attribute>
	</xs:complexType>
